# Copy to .env (gitignored) and set to your host's ids. Running the containers as
# the host user keeps everything they write under caches/ — the cache git+DVC
# repo, manifests, cached bytes — host-owned instead of root-owned, so the
# operator can manage them and the webui's git/dvc never leaves root-owned files.
#
#   PKGCACHE_UID=$(id -u)
#   PKGCACHE_GID=$(id -g)
#   DOCKER_GID=$(stat -c %g /var/run/docker.sock)   # lets the non-root webui use docker
PKGCACHE_UID=1000
PKGCACHE_GID=1000
DOCKER_GID=999

# Break-glass superuser for the console. SETTING THESE TURNS ON control-plane auth
# (login + account/ownership enforcement); leave them unset to keep the API open on
# a trusted network. Verified from the environment on every login, never written to
# the users store, and can't be demoted or deleted — the always-present root that
# bootstraps the first accounts. Use a strong, unique password (not the username).
# UI_ROOT_USER=admin
# UI_ROOT_PASSWORD=change-me-to-something-long

# Shuttle staging dir (constant). Exports are written to <dir>/out and imports
# are read from <dir>/in; you copy out/ onto removable media and drop it into in/
# on the other machine. Defaults to ./shuttle inside the repo (mounted + writable
# by you). Must be writable by PKGCACHE_UID. Override to relocate it:
# PKGCACHE_SHUTTLE=/home/youruser/pkgcache-shuttle
